Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer II* position with *Airlines Reporting Corporation (ARC)*. I bring over three years of professional experience building full-stack distributed systems, cloud-native microservices, and production backend platforms, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the full-stack, cloud-native engineering depth this role demands — spanning AWS serverless services, microservices architecture, and CI/CD-driven Agile delivery. At Sperse, I architected a full-stack, distributed multi-agent CRM platform using Python, LangGraph, and FastAPI with a React frontend, routing 10,000+ users across 40+ microservices-decomposed sub-agents with JWT-propagated tenant-aware access control. Alongside it, I designed a stateless, containerized MCP server exposing 160+ API Gateway-style tool endpoints with OpenTelemetry observability, and built GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines aligned with Scrum sprint cadences — running trace-based evals to gate every release on latency, accuracy, and safety. I also developed a React and TypeScript visual workflow platform backed by Temporal for durable execution and Redis-powered real-time status tracking. At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic, stateless Storage Service in Java and Spring Boot handling file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — applying disposable and reactive distributed patterns — and orchestrated long-running jobs with AWS Step Functions and Lambda, achieving fault-tolerant error recovery across 100K+ weekly executions. I also improved full-stack scalability through PostgreSQL optimization paired with React visualizations for business stakeholders, bridging server-side performance with front-end data delivery. Together, these roles have prepared me to deliver and maintain production-grade software across the full product stack, from front-end interfaces to server-side APIs and cloud infrastructure, and to drive impact within an Agile engineering team.

I have consistently demonstrated the ability to translate business requirements into sustainable technical solutions with minimal guidance — partnering with product owners to align architecture with business needs, and sharing knowledge by clearly articulating technical decisions to non-technical stakeholders. This collaborative approach mirrors the cross-functional partnership and knowledge-sharing culture that allow product owners, business SMEs, and engineers at ARC to align on scalable solutions quickly.

I have always been passionate about *accelerating global air travel growth and connecting stakeholders across the travel ecosystem through forward-looking data and flexible distribution services*, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *using data and technology to innovate how the world travels*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

